dct_description_sm: a M. Seuttero ; Tob. Conr. Lotter sculps.
Coordinates approximate and based on Greenwich meridian.
4 bar scales on map given in "Stadia", "Mille passus geometrici", "Milliaria unais horae", "Dietae".
Shows topography, drainage, territories of the tribes of Israel, places of historical interest.
2 decorative cartouches with illustrations of holy men and biblical references.
Appears in Seutter's Grosser Atlas. Augsburg, 1741?
